RATE OPERATIONAL VARIANCE\":\"Labour rate operational variance compares the revised standard rate per hour to the actual rate per hour and multiplies the difference by the number of hours worked.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT FOR ACCOUNTANCY TEACHING CO (AT CO) IN 20X9\":\"The Accountancy Teaching Co (AT Co) faced a 20% decline in demand for accountancy training in 20X9, leading to smaller class sizes. Despite this, AT Co improved its service quality through several developments, including a 24-hour student helpline, an interactive website, a new staff training program, and electronic systems for student enrolment and marking. These improvements were expected to reduce marking costs by $4m.\"", "\"DEVELOPMENTS AT AT CO\":\"Developments at AT Co in 20X9 included a new 24-hour student helpline, an interactive website, a new staff training program, an electronic student enrolment system, and an electronic marking system. These improvements aimed to enhance service quality and reduce costs.\"", "\"COST OF SALES\":Cost of sales, also known as cost of goods sold (COGS), represents the direct costs attributable to the production of the goods sold by a company. For the year 20X9, the expected cost of sales was $47.738 million, but the actual cost of sales was $42.056 million, showing a reduction of $5.682 million.", "\"INDIRECT EXPENSES\":\"Indirect expenses are costs that are not directly tied to the production of goods or services, such as marketing, property, staff training, and other operational costs.\"", "\"NET OPERATING PROFIT\":\"Net operating profit\" is the profit earned from a firm's normal core business operations, excluding deductions of interest and tax. Recently, net operating profit fell from $3.635 million to $2.106 million. Despite this decline, the outcome was viewed positively considering the challenging market conditions.", "\"FREELANCE LECTURERS\":\"Freelance lecturers are non-employee instructors hired by the company to teach students when there are not enough of the company's own lecturers to meet tuition needs.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT OF AT CO IN 20X9\":\"The performance assessment of AT Co in 20X9 involves evaluating various financial and non-financial metrics, including revenue, cost of sales, gross profit, indirect expenses, and net operating profit, as well as non-financial performance indicators such as student transfer rates, late enrolments, exam pass rates, labor turnover, and student complaints.\"", "\"FREELANCE LECTURER COSTS\":\"Freelance lecturer costs fell by $2.188m, contributing to the overall reduction in cost of sales.\"", "\"ONLINE MARKING SYSTEM\":\"The online marking system was expected to cut costs by $4m, but it likely saved $3.494m, contributing to the reduction in cost of sales.\"", "\"MARKETING COSTS\":\"Marketing costs are the expenses related to promoting and selling a new product. In 20X9, marketing costs increased by 42.1%, which was essential for attracting new students and improving service awareness.\"", "\"PROPERTY COSTS\":\"Property costs remained largely the same in both years.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}